Status of all Azure services world-wide:
https://status.azure.com/status

Azure blog:
https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/blog/#trending

New updates on Azure:
https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/updates/

Part of the Azure blog, provides a weekly news-letter of product announcements and road-map updates:
https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/blog/topics/last-week-in-azure/

 
Microsoft MVP Chris Pietschmann runs a blog, Build5Nines.com, that’s one of the world’s best Azure educational
resources.
https://build5nines.com/category/weekly/

What’s especially cool about Azure Weekly is that the entire back-issue archive (since 2014) is accessible and searchable on the website — absolutely for free.
https://azureweekly.info/

Azure Friday is a weekly video series hosted by Scott Hanselman (a Microsoft Product evangelist famous for his ability to provide simple explanations for Complicated technical subjects) or one of his colleagues.
https://channel9.msdn.com/Shows/Azure-Friday

Azure Architecture center
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/architecture/

Azure Rest API browser
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/rest/api/

Microsoft @ edX
https://www.edx.org/learn/azure

Microsoft Learn
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/learn/

Microsoft Worldwide Learning Certification and Exam Offers page
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/learn/certifications/deals

MeasureUp is Microsoft’s only authorized practice exam provider
https://www.measureup.com/azure-products

Visit Meetup.com and search for Azure user groups in your area.
https://www.meetup.com/topics/azure/

Microsoft Reactor (https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/reactor/), which is a Microsoft-run community
hub listing free meetups for learners and community organizers. The subject matter covers Azure and most other Microsoft technologies and job roles.


